No fewer than  20 governorship  candidates in  Bauchi State have signed an agreement to ensure peaceful polls in the state. The Resident Electoral Commissioner (REC) in the state, Mr. Ibrahim Abdullahi,said at the agreement signing that  peace accord is crucial to  democratic practice. The commissioner urged the candidates to play politics by the rules and abide by the code of conduct. The commission, he pledged, would continue to be neutral, professional and efficient in the electoral process. The event  was done under the auspices of the  Inter-Agency Consultative Committee on Election Security(ICCES) in Bauchi.